{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17603919","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17603919"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T12:45:40+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T12:45:40+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15786"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"15786","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/15786"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.12,0.24,0.28,0.28,0.08]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8477"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"62581"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"8477","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/8477"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15786"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"48028"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4934"},{"type":"tags","id":"4940"},{"type":"tags","id":"4942"},{"type":"tags","id":"4946"},{"type":"tags","id":"8497"},{"type":"tags","id":"8499"},{"type":"tags","id":"8684"},{"type":"tags","id":"10554"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"20378"},{"type":"contributions","id":"20380"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"62581","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/62581"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003ESertoli cells are essential supporting cells found in the seminiferous tubules of the testes.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes a primary function of Sertoli cells?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Phagocytosis of residual sperm cytoplasm","Production of testosterone","Synthesis of inhibin B inhibitor","Generation of primary spermatocytes","Secretion of anti-mullerian hormone in adults"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPhagocytosis of residual sperm cytoplasm\u003C/strong\u003E is a key function of Sertoli cells. As spermatids mature, they shed excess cytoplasm which Sertoli cells remove through phagocytosis.\u003C/p\u003E        \u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EProduction of testosterone\u003C/strong\u003E is performed by Leydig cells, not Sertoli cells. \u003Cstrong\u003ESynthesis of inhibin B inhibitor\u003C/strong\u003E is incorrect terminology - while Sertoli cells do produce inhibin B, there is no \u0027inhibitor\u0027 of it. \u003Cstrong\u003EGeneration of primary spermatocytes\u003C/strong\u003E occurs through meiosis of spermatogonia, not by Sertoli cells. \u003Cstrong\u003ESecretion of anti-mullerian hormone in adults\u003C/strong\u003E is incorrect as anti-mullerian hormone is primarily produced during foetal development.\u003C/p\u003E        \u003Cp\u003EOther important functions of Sertoli cells include:    \u003Cul\u003E        \u003Cli\u003EFormation of the blood-testis barrier\u003C/li\u003E        \u003Cli\u003EProvision of nutrients to developing sperm cells\u003C/li\u003E        \u003Cli\u003ESecretion of regulatory proteins like inhibin B\u003C/li\u003E        \u003Cli\u003EStructural support within seminiferous tubules\u003C/li\u003E    \u003C/ul\u003E\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Sertoli cells provide structural and nutritional support for developing sperm cells in the seminiferous tubules","Sertoli cells form the blood-testis barrier through tight junctions","Sertoli cells phagocytose residual cytoplasm from maturing spermatids"],"references":["Lara NLEM, Costa GMJ, Figueiredo AFA, de Fran\u00e7a LR. The Sertoli cell: what can we learn from different vertebrate models? Anim Reprod. 2020 May 22;16(1):81-92. doi: 10.21451/1984-3143-AR2018-125. PMID: 33299481; PMCID: PMC7720927","Peng YJ, Tang XT, Shu HS, Dong W, Shao H, Zhou BO. Sertoli cells are the source of stem cell factor for spermatogenesis. Development. 2023 Mar 15;150(6):dev200706. doi: 10.1242/dev.200706. Epub 2023 Mar 20. PMID: 36861441; PMCID: PMC10112922","Ansell, I. D. (2012). Atlas of male reproductive pathology (Vol. 10). Springer Science \u0026 Business Media","Wong WJ, Khan YS. Histology, Sertoli Cell. [Updated 2022 Nov 14]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK560631/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"48028"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15786"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"48028","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/48028"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-11-17T23:22:15+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-11-17T23:23:18+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8477"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"62581"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":nu